## Required Tests

Per project conventions, new behavior requires test coverage. Suggested test cases — mark `@pytest.mark.slow` for anything requiring a DB (testcontainers Postgres), `@pytest.mark.fast` for pure unit tests.

### Migrations (`@pytest.mark.migration`)
- Control plane migration creates `public_libraries` table with correct schema
- Tenant migration adds `is_public` column with `DEFAULT false`; existing rows unaffected

### Middleware (`@pytest.mark.slow`)
- Authenticated request with valid API key → resolves tenant, `is_public_request=False`
- Unauthenticated GET `/v1/libraries/{id}` where library is public → resolves tenant, `is_public_request=True`
- Unauthenticated GET `/v1/libraries/{id}` where library is private (no `public_libraries` row) → 401
- Unauthenticated GET `/v1/assets/page?library_id={public_id}` → resolves via `library_id` query param
- Unauthenticated GET `/v1/assets/{id}/artifacts/thumbnail?public_library_id={public_id}` → resolves via `public_library_id` query param
- Unauthenticated GET `/v1/search?library_id={public_id}` → resolves via `library_id` query param
- Unauthenticated POST (any route) → 401, never reaches public resolution
- Unauthenticated GET non-eligible route (e.g. `/v1/jobs/next`) → 401

### PATCH library toggle (`@pytest.mark.slow`)
- `PATCH /v1/libraries/{id}` with `{"is_public": true}` → `is_public=true` in response, row inserted in `public_libraries`
- `PATCH /v1/libraries/{id}` with `{"is_public": false}` → `is_public=false` in response, row removed from `public_libraries`
- Toggling back and forth maintains invariant each time
- `PATCH` with no `is_public` field → `public_libraries` unchanged

### Handler-level `is_public` verification (`@pytest.mark.slow`)
- GET public library with `is_public=true` in tenant DB → 200
- GET public library with `is_public=false` in tenant DB but stale `public_libraries` row → 404 (handler check catches it)
- GET asset with `public_library_id` pointing to correct public library → 200
- GET asset with `public_library_id` pointing to a different library (cross-library attack) → 403
- GET asset with `public_library_id` pointing to a private library → 404

---

## Environment Variable Behavior After This Change

| Env | Dev | Production |
|-----|-----|------------|
| `VITE_API_KEY` set | Used as fallback if no localStorage key | Not needed; login page handles it |
| `VITE_API_KEY` empty | Login page shown on first visit | Login page shown on first visit |

`VITE_API_KEY` remains supported as a convenience for local dev. Set it in `.env.local` and the login page is bypassed for that browser. Do not set it in CI builds or production; the login page is the intended auth path.
